In theory, I cannot disagree with this, but I think it is unprovable.
Pankseep argues that what appears to be fear in rats and humans is likely to feel the same in both cases: How, however, can one check whether rats and humans feel the same when they behave similarly?
A cockroach flees in danger if she too feels fear?
