The drivers, who can relapse due to alcohol levels, will have to install the 'Alcolock'.
The authority orders that the driver, who had three official penalties for alcohol levels, installs this system in his car, which forbids him to start the car in a drunken state. If he is alcoholic, the car does not start.
The initiative was announced last month in June and is already part of the report of the Prosecutor General's Office. According to her, it is a pilot project that will last for a year.
The purpose is to re-socialize the driver, which is why he gets a course for the re-education of traffic behaviour.
In addition to the Attorney General's Office, experience has shown that the Ministry of Transport and the Foundation of the Technical Institute for Automobile Safety will also participate in it.
According to statistics, between 30-75% of drivers reported more than once because of driving under the influence of alcohol were re-driving.
The 'alcolock' would prevent this because it is a system connected to the car, it measures the alcohol content in the exhaled air and prevents car start when the driver has taken alcohol test; or if an alcohol concentration is detected that is higher than allowed.
It costs more than EUR 1 000, and the costs are borne by the person imposing the penalty.
In this context, a study carried out in the USA in 2007 has shown that cars equipped with these devices prevent up to 65% of the standard violations already in the first year after its introduction.
In Spain, 115 lives are expected to be saved each year.
The measure is limited to administrative sanctions for two reasons: to tackle this behaviour before it becomes a criminal offence.
And in order to facilitate their implementation, a legal reform can be implemented by ordinary means, and yet a reform of the Basic Law is required, which is necessary for the prosecution process.
The device is still available in the Spanish markets, in no store, although it has already been installed in some commercial vehicles and vehicles of public transport.
