According to the English press, the government would take over all current loans from Bradford and Bringley, of which more than 41 billion (75.5 billion US dollars) from real estate loans.
The Spanish bank Santander announced yesterday that it would buy the UK bank's branches and customer accounts.
After Northern Rock, Bradford and Bringley would be the second bank to be nationalized by the British government since the beginning of this financial crisis.
