In the consumer goods sectors, a price increase of 6.8 percent was noted, while in the capital goods, a price reduction of 1.4 percent was noted.
Industrial export prices measured in Forint rose by 1.1 percent in August compared to the previous month, but there was a fall of 3.9 percent year-on-year.
